text: Bobby Wilson (29 November 1934 – 17 September 2003) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League (VFL). == Notes == == External links == * * Category:1934 births Category:2003 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Fitzroy Football Club players Category:Brunswick Football Club players
